<br>
1) Haste -- if you can get better haste, your agro will go higher than someone who doesn't have it.<br>
<br>
2) Chanter agro buffs -- I can't emphasize enough how big a difference these make.<br>
<br>
Wavecrasher has been discussed enough here that you should be able to get one. But let me tell you, my guild has two active 60 warriors, me and another guy. I have a CoF, he has an RBB, I have a CBoL and a Jade Mace, he has a CBoL and a Wavecrasher. We trade MA duties off, and yesterday were in Sky on the 5th island. I was botting a cleric, so he was MA for that, but I was getting a lot of the DT's he wanted, with me not taunting at all and sometimes not even 100% on the mob because it would move while I was healing someone. I think the main factor there was haste. I would have switched to lower delay weapons but one of us needed to get the DT and it didn't really matter which of us it was, it's just that the Wavecrasher wasn't keeping him as high on the list in a lot of cases. That was with Avatar, so presumably he was at max dex.<br>
<br>
Daramin Anklebiter<br>
Warlord of Xev<br>
